dc:title: Walls of Rome - Part destroyed by the Goths, and rebuilt under Belisarius, c. AD 520 (?)  Between the Porta del Popolo and Porta Pinciana.  Under the wall is a part of the arcade of the Aqua Virgo, the old line of which passed along on this bank.  (Procopius, de Bello Gothico, lib. i. c. xxiii. and lib. ii. c. ix.)
